        <!-- Brief Section -->
        <section class="mb-5">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-8">
                <h2 class="text-primary">Brief on TNTSE</h2>
                <p>
                  Takshila Institute has been conducting TNTSE every year to mentor and guide
                  aspiring students, to apprise them of their current level of preparations and to
                  take them to a level where they can achieve desired level of performance.
                </p>
                <p>
                  TNTSE is a scholarship test, started in 2008 by Takshila Institute for the
                  aspirants who are preparing for success in School / Board Examinations /
                  competitive examinations in Foundation courses and Engg. / Medical entrance
                  examinations like MVPY/ NTSE / JEE – Main / Advanced & NEET.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Syllabus like MAT and SAT are also covered along with all the subjects required
                  for scoring good marks in examinations.
                </p>
                <h2 class="text-primary">Why TNTSE</h2>
                <p>
                  Top scholars need the best of the content and faculties to attain / achieve high
                  goals in life. In TNTSE, participation of students is from all schools and that’s
                  the only way to judge the excellence. All the standards are participating on a
                  common platform to prove their mettle. Best brains get a chance to study under a
                  highly competitive environment. As a token of appreciation, Takshila Institute
                  provides scholarships in different courses to the students who clear the
                  benchmarks. Small batches are formed to ensure One - To - One mapping of students
                  with faculties. Daily / Weekly / Fortnightly / Monthly / Quarterly / Semi and
                  Annual tests are conducted to ensure the quality of the output is intact.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-4">
